description:
Why: All new message methods need fixture JSON files and wiremock tests per the project testing philosophy (independent oracle, no fabricated values).

What: Create hand-written fixture files and corresponding tests in methods_test.rs for: message_set_update (body edit), message_set_update (reaction add), message_set_update (delete), message_set_destroy, message_query_changes, message_query (with text filter), message_query (with threadRootId filter).

Algorithm:

Step 1 — Create fixture files in crates/jmap-chat/tests/fixtures/methods/:

message_set_update_response.json (reuse for all update variants — a SetResponse with updated map):
{
  "methodResponses": [["Message/set", {
    "accountId": "account1",
    "oldState": "state-msg-001",
    "newState": "state-msg-002",
    "updated": { "01HV5Z6QKWJ7N3P8R2X4YTMD42": null }
  }, "r1"]],
  "sessionState": "sess-abc"
}

message_set_destroy_response.json (SetResponse with destroyed list):
{
  "methodResponses": [["Message/set", {
    "accountId": "account1",
    "oldState": "state-msg-001",
    "newState": "state-msg-002",
    "destroyed": ["01HV5Z6QKWJ7N3P8R2X4YTMD42"]
  }, "r1"]],
  "sessionState": "sess-abc"
}

message_query_changes_response.json (QueryChangesResponse):
{
  "methodResponses": [["Message/queryChanges", {
    "accountId": "account1",
    "oldQueryState": "msg-qs-000",
    "newQueryState": "msg-qs-001",
    "removed": [],
    "added": [{"id": "01HV5Z6QKWJ7N3P8R2X4YTMDCC", "index": 0}]
  }, "r1"]],
  "sessionState": "sess-abc"
}

Step 2 — Add tests to crates/jmap-chat/tests/methods_test.rs:

Test 30: message_set_update (edit body) — body_json matcher verifies:
- methodCalls[0][1] has 'update': { '01HV5Z6QKWJ7N3P8R2X4YTMD42': { 'body': 'Hello, edited!' } }
- Response: new_state is 'state-msg-002', updated map contains the message ID

Test 31: message_set_update (add reaction) — body_json matcher verifies:
- patch has key 'reactions/01HVREACTIONULID01': {'emoji': '👍', 'sentAt': '<timestamp>'}

Test 32: message_set_destroy — body_json matcher verifies:
- methodCalls[0][1] has 'destroy': ['01HV5Z6QKWJ7N3P8R2X4YTMD42']
- Response: destroyed list contains the ID

Test 33: message_query_changes — verifies:
- Response: added list has one item with the expected id

Test 34: message_set_destroy rejects empty ids — no mock needed, guard fires before network

Step 3 — Update fixtures README.md table to include the 3 new fixtures.

Note: Use MessageUpdateInput and ReactionChange from the completed beads. Import them at the top of methods_test.rs.
Note: For the reaction body_json test, use a fixed UTCDate string and a fixed senderReactionId so the test is deterministic.
